类
说明
ActiveActor
Abstract class representing an active actor in the game.
ActiveActorDestructible
Abstract class for active actors that are destructible.
ActiveActorManager
Manages the active actors in the game, including friendly units, enemy units, user projectiles, enemy projectiles, ammo boxes, and hearts.
ActorSpawnerManager
Manages the spawning of various actors (such as enemies, projectiles, ammo boxes, and hearts) in the game.
AmmoBox
The AmmoBox class represents an ammo box object in the game.
AudioManager
Manages the audio functionalities of the game, including background music and sound effects.
Boss
The Boss class represents a boss enemy in the game, extending the FighterPlane class.
BossFirePattern
The BossFirePattern class controls the firing patterns of the boss in the game.
BossHealthBar
A standalone class representing the Boss's health bar using an HBox layout.
BossProjectile
The BossProjectile class represents a projectile fired by a boss in the game.
Boundary
The Boundary class represents the boundaries of the game area.
CleanDestroyedManager
Manages the cleanup of destroyed actors in the game, removing them from the scene when they go out of bounds or are marked as destroyed.
CollisionManager
Manages the collision detection and handling for various actors in the game.
Control_Animation
Controller class responsible for handling animations and interactions of the plane, bullets, enemies, and boss in the game.
Control_Control
The Control_Control class is responsible for managing the control panel in the game.
Control_EndGameMenu
The Control_EndGameMenu class handles the actions when the game ends.
Control_Main
The Control_Main class handles the main user interface of the game, including the buttons for starting the game, opening settings, and viewing control information.
Control_PauseMenu
The Control_PauseMenu class handles the functionality of the pause menu in the game.
Control_Setting
The Control_Setting class manages the settings interface in the game, including toggling background music and explosion sound effects, and handling the close functionality for the settings window.
Control_Start
The Control_Start class is responsible for controlling the game's start process, including launching and transitioning between levels.
Destructible
Interface for objects that can be destroyed or damaged.
EndGameMenuManager
Manages the end game menu and transitions when the player wins or loses the game.
EnemyPlane
The EnemyPlane class represents an enemy plane in the game.
EnemyProjectile
The EnemyProjectile class represents a projectile fired by an enemy plane.
ExplosionEffectManager
Manages the explosion effects, including the explosion image and sound.
FighterPlane
The FighterPlane class represents a fighter plane in the game.
GameOverImage
A custom class for displaying the "Game Over" image on the screen.
Heart
The Heart class represents a collectible heart object in the game.
HeartDisplay
A class that manages the display of hearts in the game.
LevelFour
Represents the fourth level of the game.
LevelOne
Represents the first level of the game.
LevelParent
Abstract class representing the parent level in the game.
LevelThree
Represents the third level of the game, where the player faces more enemies and the boss.
LevelTwo
Represents the second level of the game, which includes the player, enemies, and the boss.
LevelView
Represents the view layer of the level, responsible for displaying hearts, win and game over images, and updating the UI as the game progresses.
LevelViewLevelFour
Represents the level view for Level 4, responsible for managing and displaying elements such as the shield image, boss health bars, and other level-specific UI elements.
LevelViewLevelOne
Represents the level view for Level 1, responsible for managing and displaying elements such as the score board and other level-specific UI elements.
LevelViewLevelThree
Represents the level view for Level 3, responsible for managing and displaying elements such as the boss health bar, shield, scoreboard, and other level-specific UI elements.
LevelViewLevelTwo
Represents the level view for Level 2, responsible for managing and displaying elements such as the boss health bar, shield, hint, and other level-specific UI elements.
Main
The main entry point of the Sky Battle game application.
MutationBoss1
The MutationBoss1 class represents a specific type of mutated boss in the game.
MutationBoss2
The MutationBoss2 class represents a specific mutation of the boss enemy in the game.
MutationBoss3
The MutationBoss3 class represents a mutated version of a boss enemy in the game.
MutationBossProjectile1
The MutationBossProjectile1 class represents a projectile fired by MutationBoss1.
MutationBossProjectile2
The MutationBossProjectile2 class represents a specific type of projectile fired by the mutated boss 2 in the game.
MutationBossProjectile3
The MutationBossProjectile3 class represents a specialized projectile fired by the MutationBoss3.
PauseMenuManager
Manages the pause menu in the game, including pausing and resuming the game, and applying/removing the blur effect to elements when the game is paused.
Projectile
The Projectile class represents a projectile in the game.
ScoreBoard
A class representing a ScoreBoard that displays the player's current kills and target kills.
ShieldImage
A class representing a shield image in the game.
TargetLevel
Represents the target hint message displayed to the player during the game level.
UserInputManager
Manages user input for controlling the player's plane and handling interactions such as movement, shooting, and pausing the game.
UserPlane
The UserPlane class represents the player's controlled plane.
UserProjectile
The UserProjectile class represents a projectile fired by the user's plane.
UserProjectile.ProjectileProperties
Inner class that represents the properties of a projectile at different power levels.
WinImage
This class represents the "You Win" image that appears when the player wins the game.
